comments[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-16T20:25:22.624Z",codex-wide-sdk-20260716,"Implementation start 2026-07-16: replace the module-level mutable Commander graph with invocation-owned program state and prove extension commands/flags cannot leak between sequential in-process runs."
  "2026-07-16T21:18:25.844Z",codex-wide-sdk-20260716,"Evidence: runPmCli now constructs and lifecycle-hooks a fresh Commander graph on every in-process invocation. The persistent worker bridge no longer detects/disposes tainted state, and the cross-workspace regression proves an extension-injected list flag from workspace A is absent in workspace B. Linked test passed; full repository coverage passed 294 files / 5,751 tests at exact 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-16T21:34:47.688Z",codex-wide-sdk-20260716,"Pre-push Greptile review 95f483bd-d4a2-4019-a3a4-f57ca1f0cd21 completed at confidence 4/5 and safe-to-merge. Accepted its sole P2: indented the full attachProgramLifecycleHooks body for readable block structure. Focused re-entrancy test, strict ESLint, static/docstring, package-boundary, and token gates pass after the fix."
  "2026-07-16T22:10:04.293Z",codex-wide-sdk-20260716,"Hosted review follow-up evidence: accepted all invocation-isolation findings. The regression now awaits runCliInProcess twice, pager environment mutations restore in runPmCli finally, empty inline authors fail usage validation, path values beginning with option syntax stay literal, extension legacy actions only rewrite the command token, and --type parsing respects the argument terminator. Focused CLI suites passed 217 tests; full repository coverage passed 296 files / 5,758 tests at exact 100/100/100/100."
